      "id": "fs-idp13681744",
      "class": "top-titled",
      "summary": "The table provides solutes and solvents for a variety of solutions. In air, the solute is O subscript 2 g and the solvent is N subscript 2 g. In soft drinks, the solute is C O subscript 2 g and the solvent is H subscript 2 O l. In hydrogen in palladium, H subscript 2 g is the solute and P d s is the solvent. In rubbing alcohol, H subscript 2 O l is the solute and C subscript 3 H subscript 8 O l or 2 – propanol is the solvent. In saltwater, N a C l s is the solute and H subscript 2 O l is the solvent. In brass, Z n s is the solute and C u s is the solvent.",
