          "media": {
            "id": "fs-idm50751088",
            "alt": "Two figures are shown. The first contains two spherical containers joined by a closed stopcock. The container to the left is labeled H e. It holds about thirty evenly dispersed, small, light blue spheres. The container on the right is labeled A r and contains about thirty slightly larger blue-green spheres. The second, similar figure has an open stopcock between the two spherical containers. The light blue and green spheres are evenly dispersed and present in both containers.",
            "src": "../../media/CNX_Chem_11_01_HeArsol.jpg",
            "mimeType": "image/jpeg"
